---
title: Text Selection
section: developers

---

Text selection is controlled via the [`PSPDFTextSelectionView`][] which is part of every [`PSPDFPageView`][] via the [`selectionView`][] property.

The [`PSPDFViewControllerDelegate`][] has delegates that both allow to selectively block text selection [`shouldSelectText:withGlyphs:atRect:onPageView:`][] and to be notified whenever a text has been selected [`didSelectText:withGlyphs:atRect:onPageView:`][]

Text selection can also be disabled via the [`textSelectionEnabled`][] switch in the configuration object.

Text can be programmatically selected via setting [`selectedGlyphs`][] or [`selectedImage`][] for image selection. Nil out these properties to clear any current selection.

